  "text": "This together with (29) and (30) implies thatĉ(q) ≥c(q) for all q ∈ [0, 1]. Therefore, for δ = 1 the first-best can be implemented by Proposition 3, whenever diagnosis effort is optimal in the first-best. 30 The argument is the same as in the standard moral hazard model à la [CITATION_1] that the agent will exert no effort if his wage is constant and does not depend on his output.",
